  {
    "name": "a colourful countdown calendar",
    "shortName": "calendar",
    "description": "Colourful wood blocks, hand-painted with a variety of letters and numbers in bold chirography, sit neatly stacked in a lacquered display tray. Each of the pieces is stored with meticulous care, awaiting proper arrangement to display a countdown to the next special occasion. A label inside the box states: \"PUSH CALENDAR SET [days/months/years], PUSH CALENDAR OCCASION [whatever occasion], PUSH CALENDAR NUMBER [1-365], PUSH CALENDAR BEGIN, PUSH CALENDAR DOWN, and SHAKE CALENDAR to reset.\"",
    "tags": ["readable"],
    "notes": "",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "read",
        "response": "",
        "notes": "Calendar command reference text shown in-game (timestamps omitted)."
      },
      {
        "command": "shake",
        "response": "",
        "notes": "Old observed room response: You vigorously shake a colourful countdown calendar, causing all the pieces to fall back into the storage tray."
      },
      {
        "command": "push calendar set [days/months/years]",
        "response": "",
        "notes": "Set the countdown increment by days, months, or years."
      },
      {
        "command": "push calendar occasion [whatever occasion]",
        "response": "",
        "notes": "Set the occasion for the countdown display."
      },
      {
        "command": "push calendar number [number]",
        "response": "",
        "notes": "Set the starting countdown value."
      },
      {
        "command": "push calendar begin",
        "response": "",
        "notes": "Starts the countdown."
      },
      {
        "command": "push calendar down",
        "response": "",
        "notes": "Stores the calendar back with you."
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar"
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "a fractured marble shard",
    "shortName": "shard",
    "description": "Interlocking rings decorate the outer edges of this tablet fragment, the pale marble dusted with a light coating of royal blue paint which lurks in errant flecks despite the ravages of time. Evidently part of a much larger whole, the stone is both cool and finely grained, but some of its edges remain jagged where fracture and rupture take hold. Grains of sand and soil dwell within the deep grooves carved into its front side, where large chiselled lettering remains barely legible in the remnant ruin of a once grand and public proclamation.",
    "tags": ["readable"],
    "notes": "",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "read",
        "response": [
          "In the sight of the Logos, in the witness of the Church...",
          "...and may Seleucar be whole once more."
        ],
        "notes": "There are multiple shards with different text lines"
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Rakdra",
      "price": 4000
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "a philosopher's calendar",
    "shortName": "calendar",
    "description": "Cream-coloured vellum fills this calendar with dozens upon dozens of wafer-thin sheets, the smell of fresh parchment long surrendered to the faint must of age and decrepitude. Twin holes pierce the top of each page, bound together by a pair of faux bronze bands which gleam with a dull lustre. Thread of flaxen hue loops through and wraps around these punched rings, holding the item together while allowing the top sheaf to be flipped over and returned to the back of the stack when desired. Glossy images decorate each leaf and lend protection through resilient varnish, oilpaint renditions of the Mnemosyme, the Imperial City, and other Seleucarian landmarks providing a charming backdrop to the existential script spilling across the bottom in black ink.",
    "tags": ["readable"],
    "notes": "",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "read",
        "response": "To chase the future is to surrender the present.",
        "notes": ""
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Rakdra",
      "price": 8750
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "a justiciar's writ of criminal condemnation",
    "shortName": "writ",
    "description": "Riddled with the countless creases of extreme age and stained to near-yellow by exposure to time and element alike, this weathered poster joins to a narrow wooden board to resist curling or other peeling that would render it illegible. The seal of Imperial Seleucar gleams brazen in the bottom right corner, stamped on the opposite side by the mark of the Empire's Justice. Together, the staff and gavel symbology lend the authority of Empire to the piece, the sigils slightly smudged but retaining all of their pomp regardless of defacement. Bold ink spills across the page in variegated colours, combining to render the head and shoulders of the day's miscreant in unfortunate and highly unflattering caricature. Beneath the portrait, black lettering unfolds in the neat script of a stern, bureaucratic hand, the declaration enumerating the crimes and infamy of an individual deemed worthy not only of public scorn but immediate arrest, trial, and punishment for defying the law.",
    "tags": ["readable"],
    "notes": "You may try to ADJUST WRIT <name> to fill in a justiciar's writ of criminal condemnation's blank spaces, then PUSH it into place or PULL it down.",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "read",
        "response": "By the authority vested in the Hall of the Judiciary and under the watchful judgement of both law and Imperial Crown, the individual known as [name] is hereby condemned as a criminal of ill repute and public concern.\nThe aforementioned stands accused of conduct most unlawful, including a litany of high crimes, misdemeanours, and other acts disruptive to the peace, dignity, and stability of the Seleucarian Empire.\nAll loyal citizens, officials, public servants, and visitors to the Imperial City are therefore advised most strongly to treat [name] with suspicion and extreme caution, and to report any knowledge of their whereabouts to the nearest magistrate or appointed officer of the law.\nDo not attempt to take the law into your own hands. The criminal so named is extremely dangerous and Imperial Law does not recognise vigilanteism.\nSo mote it be.",
        "notes": ""
      },
      {
        "command": "adjust writ [name]",
        "response": "You scrawl the name of [name] upon a justiciar's writ of criminal condemnation, identifying them as a criminal of extreme disrepute.",
        "notes": ""
      },
      {
        "command": "push writ",
        "response": "You quickly pin up a justiciar's writ of criminal condemnation and smooth out the edges.",
        "notes": "places writ in the room"
      },
      {
        "command": "pull writ",
        "response": "You tear a justiciar's writ of criminal condemnation down and take it for your own.",
        "notes": "removes writ from the room and adds it to inventory"
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Rakdra",
      "price": 17500
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "a pair of weathered pilgrim's boots",
    "shortName": "boots",
    "description": "Crafted from toughened leather lacking embellishment or flourish, the rough style of these boots identify them as peasant wear, ill-suited to high courts or grand halls. The brown material bears patches of sweat, dust, and other detritus, stained and wizened by long exposure to the elements and the unmistakeable ravages of extended travel. Yellowed laces crisscross in haphazard loops about the front and culminate in sturdy knots. Wrapping the ankles, broad straps join to simple iron buckles, they too dulled by time and bearing signs of rust. While the toes show scuffs and shallow abrasions, the soles remain layered and thick, their hobnailed undersides built for endurance and eschewing all notions of style or elegance in the process. Some few errant threads hang loose from the outer edge yet most remain firm in a testament to garb made to last.",
    "tags": ["wearable", "footwear"],
    "notes": "",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "wear",
        "response": "You pull a pair of weathered pilgrim's boots onto your feet, the leather settling around your calves with the familiarity and ease of long travel.",
        "notes": ""
      },
      {
        "command": "remove",
        "response": "You slip free of a pair of weathered pilgrim's boots, your feet lighter without the remembered weight of the road.",
        "notes": ""
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Ordruin",
      "price": 8500
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "a reptilian scabbard",
    "shortName": "scabbard",
    "description": "Masterfully crafted from a sinuous length of scaled leather hide, this scabbard is pieced together with seamless precision. Its origin is a mystery, the luminous scales resembling those of a dragon, smooth to the touch with a mirror-like surface, but are soft and flexible unlike the armour-like plates of its brethren. Tough leather comprises the scabbard's inner lining, and a row of rubies glitters within an abstract pattern on the finely-tooled shoulder strap.",
    "tags": ["scabbard"],
    "notes": "",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "",
        "response": "",
        "notes": ""
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Eldephor",
      "price": 7500
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "a carved wooden sheath",
    "shortName": "sheath",
    "description": "Split from the dense wood of a mighty oak, this sheath is carved with the images of sprawling trees, their branches interlocking to form an uninterrupted pattern. Between the leaves peek the watchful faces of dryads, and squirrels and birds hide among the limbs. Aromatic oil is rubbed over the surface of the wood to give it a dark sheen, and a lining of lambswool within the sheath protects the edge of the blade from dulling.",
    "tags": ["sheath"],
    "notes": "",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "",
        "response": "",
        "notes": ""
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Eldephor",
      "price": 7500
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "a Seleucarian Saboteur's wrist sheath",
    "shortName": "sheath",
    "description": "Worn beneath the patina of centuries come and gone, this sheath yet boasts a sleek and dignified form, easily concealed up the sleeve or cuff to evade the notice of prying eyes. The confines themselves remain suitable for only the most clandestine of blades, the entirety of the piece little more than a handspan in length. A single raised image holds pride of place undiminished by the fall of its age, the undeniable emblem of Nicator's staff swathed in laurels made dread portent by dint of bountiful vegetation become ensnaring serpents coiled tight about Seleucarian authority.",
    "tags": ["sheath"],
    "notes": "",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "sheathe",
        "response": "You slide a steel stiletto into the narrow confines of a Seleucarian Saboteur's wrist sheath and adjust for comfort.",
        "notes": ""
      },
      {
        "command": "draw",
        "response": "You draw a steel stiletto from a Seleucarian Saboteur's wrist sheath, the blade glinting as it is set free from concealment.",
        "notes": ""
      },
      {
        "command": "touch",
        "response": "You run your fingers across a Seleucarian Saboteur's wrist sheath, carefully tracing the raised crest of Nicator's staff.",
        "notes": ""
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Ordruin",
      "price": 9500
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "a Mnemosynian backstrap",
    "shortName": "backstrap",
    "description": "Fashioned from thick leather long since softened by use, this backstrap bears all the wear of centuries in its cracked surface and wizened features. Muted pigment of blue-grey depicts the meandering course of the Mnemosyne on the front side, the line wavering deliberately from shoulder to hip in a faithful portrayal of the water's sinuous path. Some few blemishes impede the river's journey in the form of pockmarks and stains, veined obsidian carved to form narrow bands holding the piece in place. Bronze loops join with dulled rivets at measured intervals, scuffed but nevertheless retaining cohesion sufficient to bear weapon or shield in their grasp. Flattened in places, the reverse bears a lining of rough suede to prevent slippage, the seams held together with strands of royal blue thread.",
    "tags": ["backstrap"],
    "notes": "",
    //TODO "lash" and "unlash" commands for backstrap, which can be used to hold a weapon or shield on the back
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "touch",
        "response": "Your fingers trace the painted river along a Mnemosynian backstrap, following its wavering course toward the dark bands of the obsidian weir.",
        "notes": ""
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Ordruin",
      "price": 8500
    }
  },
