  {
    "name": "an ossiferous deck of tarot cards",
    "shortName": "deck",
    "description": "This deck of tarot cards lies bound between thin plates of yellow-aged bone, with blackened cords of sinew threading its corners in tight, severe stitching to form a casket etched with cadaverous renditions of the Arcana. Expertly carved into shallow grooves and darkened with soot is a skeletal Emperor wearing a crown of finger-bones, lounging upon a throne of ribs alongside a Tower of stacked vertebrae. Afore him lies the Wheel, spokes of femur and tibia leading towards a leering skull in place of its central hub. He is surrounded by ghastly hierophants and marrow-crowed tyrants, the macabre imagery capable of arresting even the most phlegmatic eye.",
    "tags": ["deck"],
    "notes": "",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "touch",
        "response": "The skeletal Emperor shifts slightly upon his throne in response to your touch, the finger-bone crown upon his head tilting a fraction before going still.",
        "notes": ""
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Rakdra",
      "price": 12500
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "an elaborate paper crown",
    "shortName": "crown",
    "description": "Crumpled cutaways of patchwork and pressed flowers line this elaborate paper crown, reinforcing the thin material beneath. Torn in several places around its border, hastily cut triangles coloured in a prismatic rainbow of gemstones aim upwards, excepting only the occasional dog-eared points scuffed with dirt and stains. A scrawled image traces across the top of a pressed flower meant to cover the forehead, forming what might be described as an attempt at drawing an open eye save for the complete lack of an iris and eyelashes extending straight down from the bottom.",
    "tags": ["wearable", "headwear"],
    "notes": "",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "wear",
        "response": "Donning an elaborate paper crown, you feel buoyed by a new sensation of confidence in your regal appearance.",
        "notes": ""
      },
      {
        "command": "remove",
        "response": "With a sigh, you remove an elaborate paper crown and relegate yourself once more to the ranks of the peasantry.",
        "notes": ""
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Eldephor",
      "price": 2500
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "a sun-bleached bone gemshorn",
    "shortName": "gemshorn",
    "description": "Plucked from the scorched sands of Garash's Grief, a curved handful of bone sunscoured to a pristine white hue bears itself as the body of a pastoral instrument, seven uniform holes punched into its length in a graceful crescent. The wide end of the horn bears a petrified wooden fipple plug encompassed by a broad band of twisted silver thread, a simple leather loop tucked underneath to allow easy carrying. Etched across the back of the piece, a beautiful trailing motif of the sun and moon intertwining runs all the way from the browned tip of the horn to terminate just before the tuning ring, a homage to the beliefs of those who call the desolate reach of the Earth Plane their home.",
    "tags": ["wearable", "instrument"],
    "notes": "",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "play",
        "response": "",
        "notes": "Musical instrument proficiency"
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Eldephor",
      "price": 20000
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "a set of archaic prayerbeads",
    "shortName": "prayerbeads",
    "description": "A set of sixteen wooden beads, measured for the members of the Seleucarian Pantheon, run along a cord of tightly braided rope, alternating in a measured sequence between painted blues and golds. Each bead bears its own subtle variation of those two colours, the tones drifting from rich cobalt to tepid azure and from warm gilt to dimmed brass, time and handling taking their tithe in varying degrees. Simple bronze hooks serve as clasps on either end, attached to a slender ring from which several frayed and straggly tassels hang precariously. When laid end-to-end, these beads are long enough to fit generously around the neck or to be wrapped around the wearer's wrist.",
    "tags": ["wearable"],
    "notes": "",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "pull",
        "response": "",
        "notes": "PULL on these beads while standing before a shrine to one of the Seleucarian Divine."
      },
      {
        "command": "brush",
        "response": "",
        "notes": "BRUSH them along with your prayer to communicate with the Gods."
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Lindire",
      "price": 12500
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "some brass judiciary scales",
    "shortName": "scales",
    "description": "Though rendered dull by the encroaching centuries since the Fall, these scales of Imperial Seleucar nevertheless retain much of their refulgent gleam, the high calibre metal polished in defiance of obsolescence it cannot quite fully resist. The sturdy frame arises like a pyramid around a foot from the ground, narrowing to a tapered point at the apex where a smithed laurel-staff symbol presides. Lengths of twinkling chain links descend from the peak and fasten to twin plates of thin brass which in turn connect to the central mechanism in an elaborate rivet. Heavy weights stand upon each side beside a pair of small plaques, the names of trangressors and miscreants aplenty etched and erased in a crisscross pattern of justice measured and meted.",
    "tags": [],
    "notes": "You may attempt to ADJUST some brass judiciary scales LEFT|RIGHT <text> in order to inscribe its weights. If both weights are inscribed, PUSH SCALES to render judgement.",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "adjust scales left|right [word]",
        "response": "You wipe clean the leftmost weight of some brass judiciary scales and engrave upon it: [word].",
        "notes": "Only a single word is allowed"
      },
      {
        "command": "push scales",
        "response": "With some brass judiciary scales's weights set, you give it a gentle nudge and hope for justice to prevail.\nThe weights within some brass judiciary scales finally settle, the burden of justice causing the leftmost side to descend more noticecably.\nThe scales of justice declare [word] to be guilty.",
        "notes": ""
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Quaen'a",
      "price": 12000
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "a scroll of imperial proclamation",
    "shortName": "scroll",
    "description": "Creamy vellum forms the basis of this scroll, the thick parchment spooling about a pair of polished alder wood rods. Weighty with the authority of Imperial Seleucar, the rollers gleam with carved laurel-crown symbols bookending a miniature depiction of the Staff of Nicator, their handles tapering to narrow points for ease of storage and use. Broad margins frame a wide expanse upon the unblemished and as-yet-unmarked page, the surface smooth and carefully prepared to receive ink. Blue silk completes the piece in the form of a narrow ribbon, looping around the centre in an elaborate knot to bind the contents closed.",
    "tags": ["writable"],
    "notes": "",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "",
        "response": "",
        "notes": ""
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Rakdra",
      "price": 7500
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "a brass officer's whistle",
    "shortName": "whistle",
    "description": "Irregular patches of tarnish darken and dull the metal of this whistle, solid brass shaped into a cylinder whose shine and shimmer both lie dulled by the advance of age. Scratch and dent conspire toward further signs of degradation, most notably along the mouthpiece and outer chamber. Through a narrow ring at one end threads a frayed length of braided cord, flexibility now consigned to stiff recalcitrance from myriad years of disuse. Remnants of imperial engraving circles the body, the laurel-crowned staff identifying it as the property of the Seleucarian military.",
    "tags": [],
    "notes": "You may wish to BLOW a brass officer's whistle, and specify a command type. 3.5s balance for blown commands",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "blow",
        "response": "You lift a brass officer's whistle to your lips and blow a clear, solitary note."
      },
      {
        "command": "blow [id] attention",
        "response": "You lift a brass officer's whistle to your lips and blow a clear, solitary note.",
        "notes": ""
      },
      {
        "command": "blow [id] advance",
        "response": "You lift a brass officer's whistle to your lips and blow a clear, solitary note.",
        "notes": ""
      },
      {
        "command": "blow [id] wheel",
        "response": "You bring a brass officer's whistle to your lips and draw out a long, rising note, ending it with a short, clipped chirp.",
        "notes": ""
      },
      {
        "command": "blow [id] salute",
        "response": "You lift a brass officer's whistle and sound three measured notes, evenly spaced and deliberate.",
        "notes": ""
      },
      {
        "command": "blow [id] reform",
        "response": "You press a brass officer's whistle to your lips and release a rapid, staccato trill.",
        "notes": ""
      },
      {
        "command": "blow [id] ease",
        "response": "You press a brass officer's whistle to your lips and release a rapid, staccato trill.",
        "notes": ""
      },
      {
        "command": "blow [id] turn",
        "response": "You raise a brass officer's whistle and sound two long, sustained notes that hang in the air.",
        "notes": ""
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Therine",
      "price": 6500
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "a minotaur calfskin scroll",
    "shortName": "scroll",
    "description": "A thin, rough sheet of minotaur calfskin provides the basis of this scroll. Its edges, torn rather than cut, are wrapped tightly over two weighted dowels of tiger maplewood, providing an unrefined, yet entirely acceptable writing surface.",
    "tags": ["writable"],
    "notes": "",
