      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar"
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "a dulkurio-ma manuscript",
    "shortName": "manuscript",
    "description": "Bound between rigid covers of scorched hide stretched taut over blackened, warped boards, this harsh manuscript bears a weight far outstripping its size. Scarred leather puckers where once iron clasps sealed the tome shut, faint impressions still visible along the edges. Dried blood clings to the spine amidst a patina of dust and grime, the environmental viscera of Anzari-tarin rendering the surface both coarse and unpleasant to the touch. Thick sheets of similarly rough vellum dwell within, spots of dark ink and half-torn parchment evincing an air of secrets kept then hastily discarded. A faint metallic tang arises from the leaves and clings to the air, the strange musk of a bygone people a legacy persisting even through extinction.",
    "tags": ["writable"],
    "notes": "",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "touch",
        "response": "You press a hand against a dulkurio-ma manuscript and feel its coarse surface and rough edges respond in kind, the poignant weight of history settling over you like a physical burden.",
        "notes": ""
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Rakdra",
      "price": 22500
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "a burnished cryptex",
    "shortName": "cryptex",
    "description": "Bronze rings, each engraved with a precise row of letters and symbols, encircle a polished oak cylinder at the heart of the device, turning with a smooth, deliberate resistance. The wood beneath is darkly varnished, its grain catching the ambient light in fine amber striations between the metal bands. At one end, a fitted brazen cap may be drawn outward and pressed back into place to conceal or set the hidden inscription within, its rim etched with subtle geometric patterns. Opposite it, a twin cap bears four narrow viewing slits marked by delicate positional indicators, awaiting a cipher code to bring the device's message into coherence.",
    "tags": [],
    "notes": "Use PUSH CRYPTEX MESSAGE <message> and PUSH CRYPTEX CODE <####> for setup, TURN CRYPTEX POSITION <1-4> <1-9> to set dials, PULL CRYPTEX to decipher, and SHAKE CRYPTEX to clear settings.",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "push cryptex message [message]",
        "response": "You have set the cryptex to encode the following message: [message].",
        "notes": "Sets a new encoded message."
      },
      {
        "command": "push cryptex code [####]",
        "response": "You have set the cipher code to: [####].\nYou pull gently on the endcap, setting your code selection.",
        "notes": "Sets a four-digit numerical code. None of the digits can be zero. PULL to lock in."
      },
      {
        "command": "shake cryptex",
        "response": "A mechanical clatter and rattle emanates from a burnished cryptex as you reset it completely with a vigourous shake.",
        "notes": "Clears the cryptex settings entirely."
      },
      {
        "command": "turn cryptex position [1-4] [1-9]",
        "response": "You turn position [1-4] on a burnished cryptex to read: [1-9].",
        "notes": "Sets one dial position at a time. First value is dial number (1-4), second is digit (1-9). 15 second balance for turn"
      },
      {
        "command": "pull cryptex",
        "response": "A series of satisfying \"clicks\" resonate from a burnished cryptex as the encoded bands shift and turn into position, revealing a decoded message.",
        "notes": "Deciphers the message once the code is set."
      },
      {
        "command": "read",
        "response": "A randomised permutation of vowels and consonants offer no semblance of meaning. The bands of script forming no discernable words known to tongue or tome, yet offer the hope of potential in some hidden message if brought into proper lexical alignment.",
        "notes": "Encoded message"
      },
      {
        "command": "read",
        "response": "Turning a burnished cryptex slowly in your hands, you study the symbols and letters upon the device and see: [message]",
        "notes": "Decoded message"
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Quaen'a",
      "price": 15000
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "a mahogany music box",
    "shortName": "box",
    "description": "Carved by hand from richly grained mahogany, the exquisite detail of this music box remains evident despite the ebb and flow of time and tides uncounted. The wood shines with the uncanny lustre of subtle magic, an enchanted treasure whose delicate mechanisms and elegant design command a timeless grace and luxurious style. Bronze filigree gleams in bands of dainty laurel motifs about the edges, framing a hinged top to which specks of dust and bygone debris cling in minute patches. Miniature roses sweep in a spiral pattern across and around the exterior, each bud, stem, and petal rendered with meticulous precision. Etched into the lid and near-faded in the sole concession to advancing centuries is a smooth engraving, the remnant flourish of its script bespeaking precious gifts given and a lover's promise kept eternal. A single disc of finely tooled silver sits within, teeth poised to play a melody of halcyon days and nostalgia for an era long abandoned to mere memory.",
    "tags": [],
    "notes": "",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "touch",
        "response": "Your fingers drift across the faded engraving upon a mahogany music box, impressions of lost lovers and ancient promises filling your thoughts.",
        "notes": ""
      },
      {
        "command": "turn",
        "response": "You wind the delicate handle of a mahogany music box, the silver mechanism answering with a soft, anticipatory click.",
        "notes": "Plays a series of musical performances. Different on each turn."
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Lindire",
      "price": 12500
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "an elegant courtier's fan",
    "shortName": "fan",
    "description": "Midnight-black silk stretches between the mahogany ribs of this elegant courtier's fan. Opened, the laurel motif embroidered in gold spreads in a striking crescent upon the luxurious ebon material. Inlaid with fine gold filigree, the wooden guards catch the light in brief, glimmering flashes. Closing it emits the soft whisper of silk brushing wood, a discreet sound suited to crowded courts and careful conversations. From the pivot hangs a tassel that completes the piece's quiet extravagance: a braided cord of black thread descending from a small gilt cap, its strands tightly twisted in an intricate knot. It is currently closed.",
    "tags": [],
    "notes": "",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "flip",
        "response": "The gentle whisper of silk gliding over wood reaches your ear as you deftly flip an elegant courtier's fan open with a flick of your wrist.",
        "notes": "Flipping open"
      },
      {
        "command": "flip",
        "response": "You twirl an elegant courtier's fan in a graceful circle and flip it closed.",
        "notes": "Flipping closed"
      },
      {
        "command": "push",
        "response": "You twirl an elegant courtier's fan in a graceful circle and flip it closed.",
        "notes": "When open"
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Quaen'a",
      "price": 8500
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "an antique armillary sphere",
    "shortName": "sphere",
    "description": "Multiple rings of polished bronze interlock and overlap to form this armillary sphere, each of its bands turning with measured precision about a miniature depiction of Achaea set at the centre. What gleam remains in the metal is little more than a dull lustre worn down by time, age and Seleucarian provenance rendering is as much an antique as a functional instrument. The known continents and islands of the world are etched in fine detail upon the globe, while surrounding halos and discs chart the motions of the heavens according to an austere, imperial-derived cosmology. Above the world proper lurks the greater architecture of the Prime firmament: stars, sun, and moon eddying in gentle, enchantment-inspired motion while three darkly regal gem-settings mark the presence of the Supernal Triad in precious stones of shimmering silver, inscrutable black, and dusky, ethereal grey. Set into the top of a polished pedestal, the astronomer's trinket sits above a square plaque inlaid with laurel filigree, whatever message it may have held long lost to the ages.",
    "tags": [],
    "notes": "",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "touch",
        "response": "You brush your fingers across the Triad upon an antique armillary sphere, cool bronze rings shifting slightly beneath your touch.",
        "notes": ""
      },
      {
        "command": "turn",
        "response": "As you turn an antique armillary sphere, the rings glide smoothly around the tiny globe of Achaea.",
        "notes": ""
      },
      {
        "command": "push",
        "response": "You gently nudge one of an antique armillary sphere's bronze rings, sending the tiny firmament wheeling.",
        "notes": ""
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Quaen'a",
      "price": 17500
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "a textured map of Seleucar City",
    "shortName": "map",
    "description": "A fine frame of polished mahogany shapes a rectangular border about the perimeter of this large map, the wood defying dust, debris, and all that might diminish its splendour with glossy varnish lending it a resplendent sheen. Rendered upon stretched canvas rather than parchment, layered pigment and raised relief marry to craft a textured portrayal of Seleucar City at the height of the Succession Wars. Exquisite detail defines the piece as priceless antique, modern treasure, and historical curiosity in equal measure, oil and ink accentuating the already precise work with an array of variegated colour and shades to lend verisimillitude. The Royal Palace lords at the centre in pale tones of ivory and yields to avenues and streets fanning outward like spokes on a great wheel. Strongholds and guild halls join the tiered ensemble and meet many more roads, landmarks, and points of interest as the city sprawls yet further out from the palatial heart. Meandering in a serpentine path from east to west, the crystalline waters of the Mnemosyne unfurl in blue-white brushstrokes, passing the King's Tomb in stark grey and the Heroes' Park in bright viridian before it ends in a northward curl.",
    "tags": [],
    "notes": "",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "touch",
        "response": "The ordered geometry of the Selicande Lycaeum glides easily beneath your touch, ordered wings of scholarly eminence no less impressive in microcosm.",
        "notes": ""
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Rakdra",
      "price": 15000
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "an enormous bronze bell",
    "shortName": "bell",
    "description": "Cast from a single mould of thick bronze, this massive bell commands attention through sheer mass alone and teems with the incontrovertible gravitas of great age married to sacred purpose. Its flared mouth yawns open, vast enough to swallow a troll's upper half with ease. The once-lustrous surface now gleams with a dull umber hue, the lower lip and surface veined with myriad streaks of green verdigris creeping along the engravings encircling the body. Remnant holy symbols and laurel motifs decorate the shoulders in neat spirals, identifying the monstrous instrument as salvage from an ancient temple or other holy site. Looped arches form the crown and allow the piece to be suspended, faint hammer marks visible along the inner throat even centuries after its forging. Hanging from the underside, chain links descend to meet an iron-bound clapper and reinforced yoke, the lightest breeze kindling hints of a voice yearning to sound once again.",
    "tags": [],
    "notes": "",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "ring",
        "response": "Grasping at the chain fastened to an enormous bronze bell's clapper, you begin focusing your strength on ringing the massive instrument.\nAn enormous bronze bell shudders faintly, releasing a weak, barely audible note.",
        "notes": "Must be on the ground. Strength doesn't seem to affect the sound."
      },
      {
        "command": "get",
        "response": "ou bring all of your strength to bear, managing to heft an enormous bronze bell.",
        "notes": "10s balance"
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Quaen'a",
      "price": 15000
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "a tarnished coin",
    "shortName": "coin",
    "description": "",
    "tags": [],
    "notes": [
      "King Valerias deSangre",
      "Queen Catarin deSangre",
      "Lucaine Pyramides"
    ],
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "polish",
        "response": "You turn a tarnished coin over in your hands, lifting the polishing cloth dangling from a coin collector's pouch, and begin the meticulous task of unveiling the brilliance hidden beneath the coin's aged patina.\nYour careful work pays off as a tarnished coin's full argent lustre slowly returns. Every ridge and engraving is revealed in sharp relief.\nAs the coin shimmers in the palm of your hand, you find the proud visage of [various] revealed upon it.",
        "notes": "Requires a coin collector's pouch from the bazaar"
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Quaen'a",
      "price": 5000
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "a deadly dessert fork of solid silver",
    "shortName": "dagger",
    "description": "Part of a dinner set now long bereft of its gastronomical siblings, this ornate fork bears the hallmarks of expert silversmithing, the fine metal losing little of its lustre despite obviously advanced age. Laurel scrollwork chases the handle and lends texture, the relief style decorating the piece in homage to the noblesse of Imperial Selecuar. Four narrow tines taper to needle-sharp precision at the opposite end, equally suited to skewering sugared fruit and honeyed confections as flesh and muscle should need arise. Only minimal scuffs show up amidst the polish, a sole concession to antiquity otherwise denied by aristocratic lethality.",
    "tags": ["weapon", "dagger"],
    "notes": "",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "touch",
        "response": "As your fingers brush against a deadly dessert fork of solid silver, the sudden impression of a vast dining hall fills your mind.",
        "notes": ""
      },
      {
        "command": "wield",
        "response": "You raise a deadly dessert fork of solid silver with a courtly flourish, its needle-sharp tines glinting with quiet, aristocratic menace.",
        "notes": ""
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Quaen'a",
      "price": 20000
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "a claque's baton",
    "shortName": "baton",
    "description": "Slender and immaculately balanced, this claque's baton is carved from a single length of pale ivory, its surface polished to a dignified, satin lustre. The shaft remains largely unadorned, smooth and straight, tapering with deliberate subtlety toward its tip. At the base rests a decorative handle of dark, lacquered wood, capped with a weighty pommel of brushed gold. The grip is encircled by fine relief work depicting layered laurel wreaths and stylised sunbursts, their rays fanning outward in disciplined symmetry. Narrow bands of gilt separate each motif, the ornamentation unabashed in its imperial regality.",
    "tags": [],
    "notes": "",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "wield",
        "response": "As you take a claque's baton into your hands, the air tightens with expectant acclaim.",
        "notes": ""
      },
      {
        "command": "turn baton up",
        "response": "With a deft and subtle flick of the wrist, you direct a claque's baton upwards.\nJubilant cheers swell in a tempest of enthusiastic acclaim!",
        "notes": ""
      },
      {
        "command": "turn baton down",
        "response": "With a deft and subtle flick of the wrist, you direct a claque's baton downwards.\nScattered boos crescendo into a chorus of ridicule and contempt as the jeers unite and rise as one.",
        "notes": ""
      },
      {
        "command": "turn baton left",
        "response": "With a deft and subtle flick of the wrist, you direct a claque's baton to the left.\nRestless muttering ripples into disgruntled grumbling as voices stir in dissent.",
        "notes": ""
      },
      {
        "command": "turn baton right",
        "response": "With a deft and subtle flick of the wrist, you direct a claque's baton to the right.\nSatisfied whispers murmur in a gentle susurrus of affirmation.",
        "notes": ""
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Quaen'a",
      "price": 12500
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "a Seleucarian snowglobe",
    "shortName": "snowglobe",
    "description": "Stained glass shapes the outline of this aged sphere, its surface a paradigm of expert craftsmanship left to falter amidst the unforgiving union of time, element, and tide. Striking colour shades the transpent exterior, the prestige of its variegated hues marred only by the occasional fleck of dust or sand clinging with determined abandon to the edge. Tiny fractures allow air to pass through the underside, a keen whistle heralding its passage. Light bends to a spectrum of flickering fronds as it passes inside, throwing the sprawling city of Imperial Seleucar into enlightened miniature within the stately dome. Streets and parks unfurl in detail around the Royal Palace and the halls of long-closed guilds, while tiny soldiers of the succession march down narrow roads in pairs.",
    "tags": [],
    "notes": "",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "touch",
        "response": "Your fingers gently brush the stained glass of a Seleucarian snowglobe, light diffusing into soft colour as the miniature city gleams beneath your hand.",
        "notes": ""
      },
      {
        "command": "shake",
        "response": "You jostle a Seleucarian snowglobe firmly, and a sudden storm of shimmering motes swirls through the dome, blanketing palace and soldiers alike.",
        "notes": ""
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Quaen'a",
      "price": 10000
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "an antique obsidian bowl",
    "shortName": "bowl",
    "description": "Tarnished brass supports the underside of this aged bowl, four stout legs smithed and shaped to exquisite detail evident even in antiquity. Crisscrossing the dark obsidian, grey veins marry with fine scratches to both decorate and degrade the basin in equal measure. Long handling dulls much of the striated black stone, its surface polished to a muted sheen of stark, unyielding austerity. The interior curves in a smooth, unbroken decline, descending to the centre and meeting the carved arms of Nikolas-then-Nicator etched with meticulous care into the bottom.",
    "tags": [],
    "notes": "",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "touch ",
        "response": "You run your fingers slowly around the rim of an antique obsidian bowl, tracing its worn edge before brushing your thumb across the carved arms set into its base.",
        "notes": ""
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Lindire",
      "price": 4000
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "terrarium",
    "shortName": "terrarium",
    "description": "Slender planks of alder wood join to panes of clear glass to form this terrarium, its sanded frame and delicate size ideal for the confines of a domestic kitchen. Subtle laurel tracery loops at the corners, the wood mellowed by years of basking upon sunlit sills. Dark soil lies in a bed behind the angled glass, the interior arranged with deliberate care and an even, level spread throughout. A simple hinge fastens to the top side, the lid fit with a transparent ceiling for easy monitoring from all angles.",
    "tags": [],
    "notes": "",
    "interactions": [
      {
        "command": "",
        "response": "",
        "notes": ""
      }
    ],
    "source": {
      "year": 2026,
      "igYear": 1000,
      "type": "Bazaar",
      "merchant": "Gilrain",
      "price": 15000
    }
  }
]
